article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 78, Jarvis Christian 39
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Taylor Smith had 17 points and 12 rebounds and Stephen F. Austin forced 28 Jarvis Christian turnovers in moving to 3-0 on the season for the first time since 2003-04 with a 78-39 win over the Bulldogs on Tuesday. Stephen F. Austin outscored Jarvis 42-16 in the paint and limited its second opponent of the year under 40 points. He was joined in double figures by Ice Asortse with 11 points, while every Lumberjack on the roster got into the game with all but two cracking the scoring column. Roman Walker led Jarvis Christian (1-4) with 10 points.
